UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Victor Manuel STUART, Defendant, Stuyvesant Insurance Company, Intervenor-Appellant. No. 30688

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Jan. 11, 1971. Robert J. Stamps, New Orleans, La., for appellant. *581Claude C. Aueoin, Asst. U. S. Atty., New Orleans, La., Gerald J. Gallinghouse, U. S. Atty., Eastern District of Louisiana, New Orleans, La., for appellee.

Before WISDOM, COLEMAN, and SIMPSON, Circuit Judges.

Rule 18, 5th Cir.; See Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Company of New York et al., 5th Cir., 1970, 431 F.2d 409, Part. I.

 PER CURIAM:

The appeal in this case is dismissed as frivolous. See Rule 20, Rules of the United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit.

Appeal dismissed.
